  codename: "Flory-Huggins LLPS — Liquid-Liquid Phase Separation for Memory"

summary: |
  Models SIFTA's memory architecture using the Flory-Huggins theory of polymer 
  solutions. Memory tokens and engrams are treated as macromolecules that undergo 
  Liquid-Liquid Phase Separation (LLPS) to form dense, localized nucleations 
  (membraneless organelles) of specific concepts.

